def visualize_graph(G):
    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, k=0.15, seed=42)  # force-directed layout

    node_colors = [G.nodes[node]["color"] for node in G.nodes]

    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))
    nx.draw(
        G, pos, node_color=node_colors, with_labels=False, node_size=50, 
        edge_color="gray", alpha=0.7
    )
    plt.show()


def create_graph(num_red = 40, num_blue = 20, p_internal = 0.2, p_external = 0.2):
    G = nx.Graph()
    E, I_red, I_blue, I = 0, 0, 0, 0

    red_nodes = range(num_red)
    blue_nodes = range(num_red, num_red + num_blue)

    # different colors indicate different communities 
    G.add_nodes_from(red_nodes, color="red")
    G.add_nodes_from(blue_nodes, color="blue")

    for u in red_nodes:
        for v in red_nodes:
            if u < v and random.random() < p_internal:
                G.add_edge(u, v)
                I_red = I_red + 1

    for u in blue_nodes:
        for v in blue_nodes:
            if u < v and random.random() < p_internal:
                G.add_edge(u, v)
                I_blue = I_blue + 1

    for u in red_nodes:
        for v in blue_nodes:
            if random.random() < p_external:
                G.add_edge(u, v)
                E = E + 1
    
    I = I_blue + I_red
    EI_global = (E-I) / (E+I)
    EI_red = (E-I_red) / (E+I_red)
    EI_blue = (E-I_blue) / (E+I_blue)

    return dict({"G":G, "EI_global":EI_global, "EI_blue":EI_blue, "EI_red":EI_red})



def permutation(G):
    all_node = list(G.nodes)
    node_colors = [G.nodes[node]["color"] for node in G.nodes]
    random.shuffle(node_colors)

    for node, color in zip(all_node, node_colors):
        G.nodes[node]["color"] = color

    E = 0
    I_red = 0
    I_blue = 0
    I = 0
    for u, v in G.edges:
        if G.nodes[u]["color"] != G.nodes[v]["color"]:
            E = E + 1
        elif G.nodes[u]["color"] == "red":
            I_red = I_red + 1
        else:
            I_blue = I_blue + 1
    
    I = I_blue + I_red
    EI_global = (E-I) / (E+I)
    EI_red = (E-I_red) / (E+I_red)
    EI_blue = (E-I_blue) / (E+I_blue)

    return dict({"G":G, "EI_global":EI_global, "EI_blue":EI_blue, "EI_red":EI_red})


def permutation_rescale(G, EI_global, EI_red, EI_blue, times = 5000, k = 0.5): # k: rescaling coefficient
    p_EI_global, p_EI_red, p_EI_blue = [EI_global], [EI_red], [EI_blue]
    
    for i in range(times):
        p_res = permutation(G)

        p_EI_global.append(p_res["EI_global"])
        p_EI_red.append(p_res["EI_red"])
        p_EI_blue.append(p_res["EI_blue"])

    rds = [] # relative deviation score
    reis = [] # resclaed EI Index

    for x in [p_EI_global, p_EI_red, p_EI_blue]:
        ma = max(x[1:])
        mi = min(x[1:])
        miu = np.mean(x[1:])
        s = np.std(x[1:])
        rd = (x[0] - miu) / s
        # erd = np.exp(-rd)
        erd = np.exp(-rd*k)
        rei = (1 - erd) / (1 + erd) 

        rds.append(rd)
        reis.append(rei)
    
    return dict({"reis": reis, "rds": rds})


def permutation_test(G, EI_global, EI_red, EI_blue, times = 5000):
    p_EI_global, p_EI_red, p_EI_blue = [EI_global], [EI_red], [EI_blue]

    for i in range(times):
        p_res = permutation(G)

        p_EI_global.append(EI_global < p_res["EI_global"])
        p_EI_red.append(EI_red < p_res["EI_red"])
        p_EI_blue.append(EI_blue < p_res["EI_blue"])

    print("the p value of EI-global is {}".format(min(1-np.mean(p_EI_global), np.mean(p_EI_global))))
    print("the p value of EI-red is {}".format(min(1-np.mean(p_EI_red), np.mean(p_EI_red))))
    print("the p value of EI-blue is {}".format(min(1-np.mean(p_EI_blue), np.mean(p_EI_blue))))

# return the same values with create_graph function
def generate_graph(ind):
    edges_file = "congress{}_edges.csv".format(ind)
    nodes_file = "congress{}_nodes.csv".format(ind)

    df_edges = pd.read_csv(edges_file, sep='\t')
    df_nodes = pd.read_csv(nodes_file, sep='\t')

    G = nx.Graph()
    E, I_red, I_blue, I = 0, 0, 0, 0

    red_nodes = df_nodes.loc[df_nodes["party_code"] == 100, "icpsr"].tolist()
    red_nodes = [int(node) for node in red_nodes]
    blue_nodes = df_nodes.loc[df_nodes["party_code"] != 100, "icpsr"].tolist()
    blue_nodes = [int(node) for node in blue_nodes]
    G.add_nodes_from(red_nodes, color="red")
    G.add_nodes_from(blue_nodes, color="blue")

    edges_matrix = df_edges[["src", "trg"]].values
    G.add_edges_from(edges_matrix)

    for u, v in G.edges:
        if (u in red_nodes and v in blue_nodes) or (u in blue_nodes and v in red_nodes):
            E = E + 1
        elif u in red_nodes:
            I_red = I_red + 1
        else:
            I_blue = I_blue + 1

    I = I_blue + I_red
    EI_global = (E-I) / (E+I)
    EI_red = (E-I_red) / (E+I_red)
    EI_blue = (E-I_blue) / (E+I_blue)

    return dict({"G":G, "EI_global":EI_global, "EI_blue":EI_blue, "EI_red":EI_red})

df_reis = pd.DataFrame(columns=["EI_global", "EI_red", "EI_blue"])
df_rds = pd.DataFrame(columns=["EI_global", "EI_red", "EI_blue"])
for year in range(81, 117):
    a = generate_graph(year)
    g = a["G"]
    if year in [81, 88, 95, 102, 109, 116]:
        g2 = g
        g2.remove_nodes_from([node for node, degree in g2.degree() if degree == 0])
        visualize_graph(g2) # deleting the nodes with d=0 when visualizing
    res = permutation_rescale(a["G"], a["EI_global"], a["EI_red"], a["EI_blue"], k=0.05, times = 500) # to save time, setting the iteration times as 500
    df_reis.loc[year-81] = res["reis"]
    df_rds.loc[year-81] = res["rds"]
